  "body": "#### Feature Description\r\n\r\nChange the tests to be disabled by default in `bootstrap.sh`.\r\n\r\n#### Use Case(s)\r\n\r\n`BUILD_TESTS` requires Python 2.7, which is not supported on newer Linuxes, and will soon not be supported. It is planned to move the tests to pure Go, but in the interim it will make it easier if this is not required by default to bootstrap a build.\r\n\r\nAdvanced users that understand the 2.7 dependencies can manually specify `BUILD_TESTS=1` to re-enable.",
